  - m_Id: 3094339652
    m_Localized: User Guide
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3094339653
    m_Localized: App User Guide
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 3094339654
    m_Localized: "How to Use\n\n1. Open the main screen and confirm that the USD/JPY quote has updated. Select 1min, 5min, or 15min, or tap Refresh to update manually.\n\n2. Enter the capital in JPY used for the estimate, your current net position in currency units, and the USD/JPY entry price. A positive quantity is long, a negative quantity is short, and 0 is flat. The app does not read your SBI Securities account, so enter the actual values manually.\n\n3. Tap SBI Margin / Update. The app gets the currently applicable USD/JPY leverage, margin rate, required margin per 10,000 currency units, minimum order size, and effective date from the official SBI Securities page and saves them on this device. This only updates calculation rules; it does not sync an account, positions, or orders, and it never places trades.\n\n4. The updated rules are used with your capital, position, and market data for AI analysis. The app also checks the result against SBI required margin and minimum order size. Estimated margin is capped at 50% of capital for Conservative Advice and 70% for Aggressive Advice. If a limit is exceeded, the size may be reduced, the direction may be adjusted, or the result may become Hold. Update again after SBI changes its margin requirements.\n\n5. Choose Conservative Advice or Aggressive Advice. Conservative mode can return Hold when evidence is weak. Aggressive mode requires the AI to choose Buy or Sell, but that does not mean the signal is strong.\n\n6. Review the chart, technical indicators, AI advice, and risk notices before making your own trading decision.\n\nNotes\n\n• Quotes update every 5 seconds; candles refresh about every 60 seconds.\n• The app does not connect to an SBI Securities account. All capital and position data is entered by the user.\n• AI advice is informational, is not investment advice, and is not guaranteed to pass SBI Securities' actual order checks.\n• If market data, rules, or advice are unavailable, check your network connection and try again."
